review_blob: Beware of this beer!  I started drinking these and I love apple cider.  I could barely tell there was alcohol in there.  Color is an Amber color with a very small amount of head that goes away almost right away.  Pretty good beer overall.

This beer has no enjoyment for me... its more like the king of water.  Drink a few of these and your stomach wont feel to well in the morning, gotta love all that carbonation.  Once again a beer to drink if you cant afford something better... but why not spend the extra $2?
Golden MGD is common here in America more for adults it seems.  Golden color, I personally dont like the aftertaste.  Good enough for a cheaper American beer.  Better than Budweiser.

I personally like Miller Lite as long as i drink it quickly and dont drink the last sip.  Like almost all American Lite beers this is almost water with a metallic taste and some alcohol.  When your spoiled with good beer sometimes when you dont have it you can really put down a beer.  But for its style being lite and the low carbs, what better can you expect?

This beer is flat for getting drunk.  Cant find much to like about it.  Very watery, typical American style beer.  But if you would like to get drunk for a cheap price, or cant afford another beer I guess this is the way to go.  A good tip I can give is to add some lime to it and it takes away a bit of the metallic taste and much easier to enjoy.

When poured a slightly tan head.  The beer is about as black a beer as you can find.  Tastes of burnt malts, chocolate, overall pleasing taste, very unique to see the almost pure black color.  A beer thats not great but I would buy again.

Picked this up randomly but was really dissapointed with the lack of taste.  The beers apperance is very nice, as well as the aroma, but there is just a lack of taste I believe due to the hop bitterness.  Very bitter beer.  For its style I would say its just average.

On tap at Roccos on 45th in Highland, IN.  Taste definetely surprised me with its hopiness and the aroma is just full of hops, truly unique aroma .  Chocolately but definetely this beer is all about the hops.  A truly great stout

12 FL PZ bottle from mid 2005.  Very strong aroma.  Very similar to wine, has a chocolate smell along with several other fruits,  Color seems be more red than brown to me with a bit of tan head.  Taste is excellent, the more bottles of it you drink the more things you feel you are tasting.  The 8.1% alcohol is hidden very well.  I find this beer to go along very good with chocolate or anything sweet you may be eating.  A very good American beer.
